udev --> device manager for Linux kernel, links information on system hardware to /dev. It automatically detects new devices available and link that to /dev accordingly

/dev -->  contaions information on all of the connected hardware on a system

D-bus  -->  sends data messages between applications, a conduit of info about what is going on the system, udv utilizes dbus to notify users and the system when new hardware is attached.



HUMAN READABLE FORMAT INFORMATION FROM /dev directory

lspci

lsusb

lscpu

lsblk
